Package info.ryankenney.jasync_driver

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AsyncTask<A,R>
    Used to define an asynchronous task (a task that uses a callback to indicate completion, as opposed to a regular method return) managed by a JasyncDriver.
    DriverBody
    Used to define the asynchronous/synchronous logic managed by a JasyncDriver instance.
    ResultHandler<R>
    A callback that handles the result of an asynchronous action.
    SyncTask<A,R>
    Used to define a synchronous task managed by a JasyncDriver.
    Task<A,R>
    The common base type of AsyncTask and SyncTask.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JasyncDriver
    The central class of the jasync-driver library.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    JasyncDriverException  
    UnstableConditionsException  
  • Error Summary 
    Error Description
    JasyncActionSubmittedInterrupt
    An Error used to interrupt execution of the JasyncDriver immediately after an asynchronous action is initiated (and the JasyncDriver is awaiting for the asynchronous callback to wake it back up).
